	     Durban – A security guard has been arrested in connection with allegations that he killed a man, who had been visiting his mother in Shallcross, near Chatsworth on Wednesday, police said. The incident occurred at about 12:30 and the 34-year-old man died at the scene after sustaining a gunshot wound to his chest, said Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane. “Chatsworth police arrested a 34-year-old suspect, who was taken to a police station for detention. He will be charged and will appear at the Chatsworth Magistrate’s Court soon,” Zwane said. The motive for the killing is unknown. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  